1.FOR FINDING THE Kth Smallest Element in a BST  -----> always use inorder traversal to reduce the time and space complexity as preorder and postorder is not optimum
2.FOR FINDING THE Kth Largest Element in a BST  -----> always use inorder traversal  in reverse order to reduce the time and space complexity
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

preorder-----------------------TC= o(n) + o( n log n)    // o(n) for traversal + 0(log n) for sorting
                               TC=0(n)                //due to use of extra vector
                               
inorder------------------------TC= o(n)     // o(n) for traversal and output is already sorted in case of BST 
                               TC=0(1)                //no use of extra vector
